Noir has no support for the logical operators || and &&. This is because encoding the short-circuiting that these operators require can be inefficient for Noir's backend. Instead you can use the bitwise operators | and & which operate indentically for booleans, just without the short-circuiting. let my_val = 5; let mut flag = 1;
if (my_val > 6) | (my_val == 0) { flag = 0;
}
constrain flag == 1; if (my_val != 10) & (my_val < 50) { flag = 0;
}
constrain flag == 0;

